.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C672FF832A9C9F88370A788F" blockId="6.[151,1437,218,675]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832A9C9F8832C67992" bold="true" box="[151,468,218,243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Justification of synonymy.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8328509F8E31847992" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[603,662,220,243]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Teuia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8328509F8E31847992" box="[603,662,220,243]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Teuia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally proposed for a single species (
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF832EA09F8E36097992" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[1195,1307,218,243]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Teuia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832EA09F8E36097992" box="[1195,1307,218,243]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. beckeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) that has a highly unusual procursus (partly wrapped around the bulbal process; Huber 2000: figs 
<date id="EA1D50C5C672FF832E8A9FAC36127876" box="[1153,1280,254,279]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1259" valueMax="1260">1259–1260</date>
) but lacks an epigynal pocket (Huber 2000: fig. 1263) and contiguous male cheliceral apophyses (Huber 2000: fig. 1262). The new species 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF832B2F9E15328A783F" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[292,408,327,350]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sepitus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832B2F9E15328A783F" box="[292,408,327,350]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">M. sepitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described below shares the distinctive morphology of the procursus and was collected only 
<quantity id="595BDBE0C672FF832A9C9E3933FF78E2" box="[151,237,362,387]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="km" value="130.0">130 km</quantity>
from the type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF83281B9E3E31B578E2" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[528,679,362,387]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Teuia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF83281B9E3E31B578E2" box="[528,679,362,387]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Teuia beckeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8329279E3E30B278E2" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[812,928,364,387]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sepitus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8329279E3E30B278E2" box="[812,928,364,387]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">M. sepitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an epigynal pocket and contiguous male cheliceral apophyses. Molecular data (Eberle 
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8328939EDD31C378C6" box="[664,721,398,423]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al.</emphasis>
, unpublished data; see Appendices 1–2) also support a position of this new species within the Southern clade of 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8328B29EE0305778AA" authorityName=": Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[697,837,434,459]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8328B29EE0305778AA" box="[697,837,434,459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mesabolivar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8329589EE6309C78AA" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[851,910,436,459]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Teuia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8329589EE6309C78AA" box="[851,910,436,459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Teuia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thus synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF832EB69EE0365B78AA" authorityName=": Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[1213,1353,434,459]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832EB69EE0365B78AA" box="[1213,1353,434,459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mesabolivar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF832F8C9EE633FB788E" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Teuia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832F8C9EE633FB788E" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">T. beckeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transferred accordingly: 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8328169E8430B9788E" authority="(Huber, 2000)" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Huber" baseAuthorityYear="2000" box="[541,939,470,495]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="beckeri" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8328169E843016788E" box="[541,772,470,495]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mesabolivar beckeri</emphasis>
(Huber, 2000)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="B7E4176CC672FF8329BD9E84370A788F" box="[950,1048,470,495]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D6B9258EC672FF832ACC9EA937D57D4E" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C672FF832ACC9EA937007BC2" blockId="6.[151,1437,218,675]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Note, however, that the name 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF83282B9EAE31497B72" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[544,603,508,531]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Teuia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF83282B9EAE31497B72" box="[544,603,508,531]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Teuia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an available name in case 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8329BB9EA8372F7B72" authorityName=": Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[944,1085,506,531]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8329BB9EA8372F7B72" box="[944,1085,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mesabolivar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is split (e.g. for the “Southern clade” in Appendices 1-2). Another genus that might be revalidated in such a context is 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF832E8B9D4C36607B56" authority="Huber, 2000" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[1152,1394,542,567]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Kaliana" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832E8B9D4C37C87B56" box="[1152,1242,542,567]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Kaliana</emphasis>
Huber, 2000
</taxonomicName>
. As indicated above (Introduction), I do not implement such drastic formal changes here for two reasons: (1) current evidence is rather limited as far as taxon sampling and support values are concerned; (2) the gain of such formal changes is dubious if the diagnosability of the resulting genera is not improved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C672FF832A9C9D8037D57D4E" blockId="6.[151,1436,722,1071]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832A9C9D8033F37B8A" bold="true" box="[151,225,722,747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Notes.</emphasis>
For recent updates on generic diagnosis and description, see Huber (2015). Most of the new species described below fit this generic concept that dates back to Huber (2000) and was further developed in Machado (2007). The two key features are (1) an epigynum with median groove or pocket (e.g., 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C672FF832E659C4837D77A52" box="[1134,1221,794,819]" captionStart="FIGURES18–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1556,1578]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,195,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1535]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES18–25. Mesabolivar acrensissp.n. (18–22; ZFMK Ar 18942–43) andM.maraba sp. n.(23–25, ZFMK Ar 18948). 18–19. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 20–21, 23–24. Epigyna, ventral and lateral views. 22, 25. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views.Abbreviations:ep, epigynal pocket; pp, pore plate; v, ‘valve’. Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202525/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C672FF832EDA9C4937EF7A52" box="[1233,1277,795,819]" captionStart="FIGURES 104–114" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1805,1827]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1784]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 104–114. Left bulbal processes, dorsal and prolatero-ventral views (104–111), epigynum, ventral and lateral views (112–113), andcleared female genitalia,dorsal view (114). 104–105.Mesabolivar macushi sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18962).106–107. M. aurantiacus (Mello-Leitão, 1930) (ZFMK Ar 18963). 108–109. M.cyaneus (Taczanowski, 1874) (ZFMK Ar 18989). 110– 114.M.spinosus (González-Sponga, 2005) (MIZA MAGS 1176). Scale lines: 0.5 (all bubal processes at same scale)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202545/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">112</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C672FF832F029C4936247A52" box="[1289,1334,795,819]" captionStart="FIGURES 223–226" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1180,1202]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,195,1158]" captionTargetId="figure@57.[151,1436,193,1159]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 223–226. Mesabolivar madalena sp. n. (223–224, ZFMK Ar 19071) and M. inmanis sp. n. (225–226, ZFMK Ar 19072). 223, 225. Epigyna, ventral views. 224, 226. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views (arrow points at V-shaped sclerite). Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202575/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">223</figureCitation>
), and (2) male cheliceral apophyses with a pair of contiguous frontal apophyses (e.g., 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C672FF8329F19C6C37427A36" box="[1018,1104,830,855]" captionStart="FIGURES18–25" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1556,1578]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,195,1532]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,193,1535]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES18–25. Mesabolivar acrensissp.n. (18–22; ZFMK Ar 18942–43) andM.maraba sp. n.(23–25, ZFMK Ar 18948). 18–19. Male chelicerae, frontal and lateral views. 20–21, 23–24. Epigyna, ventral and lateral views. 22, 25. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views.Abbreviations:ep, epigynal pocket; pp, pore plate; v, ‘valve’. Scale lines:0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202525/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 18</figureCitation>
, 118, 215). Most species that do not fit this concept are part of what is below informally described as the ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8329E19C3037547A1A" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[1002,1094,866,891]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="difficilis">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8329E19C3037547A1A" box="[1002,1094,866,891]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">difficilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group’. Several species in this group of litter-dwelling species do not share any of the diagnostic characters. However, molecular data consistently place them among 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF832B7B9CF832EE7AA2" authorityName=": Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[368,508,938,963]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832B7B9CF832EE7AA2" box="[368,508,938,963]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mesabolivar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The same is true for individual representatives of other species groups proposed below, for example in the 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF832BB19C9D311F7A87" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[442,525,975,998]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="togatus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832BB19C9D311F7A87" box="[442,525,975,998]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">togatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. In addition, it is now fairly evident that the two key features are shared by certain representatives of the closely related genus 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8328D99CA1302F7D6B" authorityName="Gonzalez-Sponga" authorityYear="1998" box="[722,829,1011,1034]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Carapoia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8328D99CA1302F7D6B" box="[722,829,1011,1034]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Carapoia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF83298F9CA130CF7D6A" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[900,989,1010,1035]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Carapoia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lutea">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF83298F9CA130CF7D6A" box="[900,989,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. lutea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8329E09CA1374C7D6A" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1003,1118,1011,1035]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Carapoia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapajos">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8329E09CA1374C7D6A" box="[1003,1118,1011,1035]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. tapajos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF832E679CA137E77D6A" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1132,1269,1010,1035]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Carapoia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF832E679CA137E77D6A" box="[1132,1269,1010,1035]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In its current scope, a morphological diagnosis that covers all species of 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C672FF8329269B4430A97D4E" authorityName=": Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[813,955,1046,1071]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C672FF8329269B4430A97D4E" box="[813,955,1046,1071]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Mesabolivar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is probably impossible.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
